-- Moscow Exchange Approves New Year Stock Trading Break Dec. 29
-- B y   T o r r e y   C l a r k
-- 2012-09-28T15:07:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-28/moscow-exchange-approves-new-year-stock-trading-break-dec-29.html
The Moscow Exchange plans to halt
stock trading on Dec. 29 for  Russia ’s New Year holidays and work
on Jan. 8, according to a statement today on the bourse’s
 website .  The bourse’s council on Sept. 19 recommended a break from
Dec. 29 through Jan. 7, as well as testing the settlement
clearing system on Jan. 4 and halting the bourse for holidays on
Feb. 23, March 8, May 1 and 9, June 12 and Nov. 4.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Torrey Clark in Moscow at 
